1
00:00:10,980 --> 00:00:13,980
(St. Anton Hospital)

2
00:00:15,320 --> 00:00:16,030
Director Chen.

3
00:00:18,230 --> 00:00:19,640
I have a few questions for you.

4
00:00:20,710 --> 00:00:21,600
Sorry.

5
00:00:21,600 --> 00:00:23,200
I'm off duty. You can come back tomorrow

6
00:00:23,248 --> 00:00:24,112
with your questions.

7
00:00:27,640 --> 00:00:30,030
I'm Yuan Hong, Division Four Chief,
Jingshi Police Department.

8
00:00:30,480 --> 00:00:32,220
I'd like to ask about Qing Miao.

9
00:00:32,220 --> 00:00:33,020
=Cases Between Us=

10
00:00:33,020 --> 00:00:33,870
(Director Chen, Head of Obstetrics)

11
00:00:33,880 --> 00:00:34,864
(St. Anton Hospital)
Who?

12
00:00:35,200 --> 00:00:37,150
Director Wu's concubine.

13
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:39,360
=Episode 3=
You were the one who delivered her baby.

14
00:00:44,600 --> 00:00:45,640
I'm not very familiar

15
00:00:46,150 --> 00:00:47,880
with the woman you mentioned.

16
00:00:47,880 --> 00:00:50,110
So I don't know much
about her situation.

17
00:00:51,640 --> 00:00:53,030
You handled her prenatal checkups?

18
00:00:53,390 --> 00:00:53,790
I did.

19
00:00:54,110 --> 00:00:55,070
Was her pregnancy normal?

20
00:00:55,320 --> 00:00:55,790
Yes.

21
00:00:56,070 --> 00:00:57,600
Morning sickness, missed periods,

22
00:00:58,200 --> 00:00:59,110
and her belly grew.

23
00:00:59,350 --> 00:01:00,110
She had

24
00:01:00,110 --> 00:01:01,390
all the usual symptoms

25
00:01:01,390 --> 00:01:02,110
of pregnancy.

26
00:01:02,640 --> 00:01:03,750
What about the delivery?

27
00:01:04,950 --> 00:01:06,640
Don't even mention it.

28
00:01:07,150 --> 00:01:09,640
She was having a difficult labor.

29
00:01:09,950 --> 00:01:11,480
When I was about to operate,

30
00:01:11,480 --> 00:01:13,070
she suddenly sat up and ran out.

31
00:01:13,070 --> 00:01:14,310
Before I could react,

32
00:01:14,310 --> 00:01:15,480
she collapsed and died.

33
00:01:15,480 --> 00:01:17,640
Director Wu fell to the floor,
screaming about ghosts.

34
00:01:17,640 --> 00:01:19,000
I was completely terrified.

35
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:19,760
I froze up.

36
00:01:20,230 --> 00:01:21,640
I didn't even know

37
00:01:21,640 --> 00:01:22,832
when they took the body away.

38
00:01:25,790 --> 00:01:26,680
What are you doing?

39
00:01:27,264 --> 00:01:28,640
You haven't told a single truth

40
00:01:28,640 --> 00:01:29,950
since you walked in.

41
00:01:29,950 --> 00:01:31,510
Qing Miao was never pregnant.

42
00:01:31,760 --> 00:01:32,640
In that case,

43
00:01:32,680 --> 00:01:34,544
let's continue this conversation
somewhere else.

44
00:01:34,976 --> 00:01:37,120
What have I done?
On what grounds are you arresting me?

45
00:01:37,120 --> 00:01:38,560
You murdered Qing Miao.

46
00:01:38,896 --> 00:01:40,120
I didn't kill her!

47
00:01:40,120 --> 00:01:41,980
You were the one
with her in the operating room.

48
00:01:41,990 --> 00:01:42,920
If not you, then who?

49
00:01:54,040 --> 00:01:55,000
She killed herself.

50
00:01:56,590 --> 00:01:57,950
She came to me

51
00:01:57,950 --> 00:01:59,480
and asked me for a favor.

52
00:02:00,544 --> 00:02:02,710
They are hundred-year-old ginseng
from Mount Changbai.

53
00:02:02,710 --> 00:02:03,680
It's a small token.

54
00:02:07,920 --> 00:02:09,360
Abortion is illegal.

55
00:02:09,560 --> 00:02:10,750
Quite the opposite.

56
00:02:10,760 --> 00:02:12,912
(Qing Miao, Daughter of Gu Xishan)
I wanted to appear pregnant

57
00:02:13,008 --> 00:02:14,360
without actually being pregnant.

58
00:02:16,310 --> 00:02:16,870
Later,

59
00:02:17,104 --> 00:02:18,960
she asked me to perform
a uterine curettage.

60
00:02:19,430 --> 00:02:20,750
I refused outright.

61
00:02:21,024 --> 00:02:21,984
But she kept threatening

62
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:24,384
to expose the fake pregnancy certificate
I issued for her.

63
00:02:24,880 --> 00:02:26,120
I had no choice but to give in.

64
00:02:26,400 --> 00:02:28,030
You were afraid she'd expose you,

65
00:02:28,816 --> 00:02:29,750
so you killed her?

66
00:02:29,750 --> 00:02:30,680
Kill her?

67
00:02:30,680 --> 00:02:31,400
I already told you.

68
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:32,750
I didn't kill her.

69
00:02:32,750 --> 00:02:33,590
I'm telling you,

70
00:02:33,590 --> 00:02:35,910
she was insane. I was just
about to begin the operation,

71
00:02:35,910 --> 00:02:37,440
and she suddenly pulled out
an earring

72
00:02:37,456 --> 00:02:38,800
and stabbed it into her own ear.

73
00:02:38,840 --> 00:02:40,020
Do you take us for fools?

74
00:02:40,030 --> 00:02:41,000
If I wanted to kill her,

75
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:42,360
I'd have had plenty of chances.

76
00:02:42,360 --> 00:02:43,200
Why would I wait

77
00:02:43,232 --> 00:02:45,280
until we were alone
in the operating room to kill her?

78
00:02:45,280 --> 00:02:46,870
Wouldn't that just
be asking for trouble?

79
00:02:54,060 --> 00:02:55,540
(St. Anton Hospital)

80
00:02:55,560 --> 00:02:57,584
She hid her identity
to marry into the Wu family.

81
00:02:57,616 --> 00:02:59,232
After learning
she had a terminal illness,

82
00:02:59,248 --> 00:03:00,416
she planned her own death.

83
00:03:00,750 --> 00:03:02,000
First, she faked a pregnancy.

84
00:03:02,240 --> 00:03:04,030
Then she poisoned the maid.

85
00:03:04,960 --> 00:03:07,520
Then came the poison
and the ghost story.

86
00:03:07,520 --> 00:03:08,630
That concubine

87
00:03:08,960 --> 00:03:10,360
really planned everything.

88
00:03:10,680 --> 00:03:12,430
She went through all this

89
00:03:13,030 --> 00:03:14,590
just to reopen

90
00:03:14,590 --> 00:03:15,710
her father's case?

91
00:03:16,030 --> 00:03:16,590
But that case

92
00:03:16,590 --> 00:03:18,360
was decided by the court
according to the law.

93
00:03:18,590 --> 00:03:20,360
I've gone through the case file.

94
00:03:20,360 --> 00:03:21,430
Someone really did die.

95
00:03:21,630 --> 00:03:22,960
It caused quite a stir.

96
00:03:22,960 --> 00:03:23,870
Without solid evidence,

97
00:03:23,870 --> 00:03:25,536
there's no way
he would've been convicted.

98
00:03:26,120 --> 00:03:28,430
Why was she so convinced
her father had been wronged?

99
00:03:29,680 --> 00:03:30,630
I don't know.

100
00:03:31,504 --> 00:03:33,150
Maybe we should ask the Supreme Court.

101
00:03:34,750 --> 00:03:35,400
Okay.

102
00:03:39,360 --> 00:03:40,400
Why are you looking at me?

103
00:03:40,560 --> 00:03:42,016
I thought you had connections there.

104
00:03:42,150 --> 00:03:42,750
You!

105
00:03:42,750 --> 00:03:43,870
You checked up on me?

106
00:03:43,870 --> 00:03:45,030
How about Tiansheng Restaurant?

107
00:03:45,750 --> 00:03:47,240
Why Tianshang Restaurant?

108
00:03:47,240 --> 00:03:48,190
Did I agree to that?

109
00:03:48,190 --> 00:03:48,630
Huh?

110
00:03:48,630 --> 00:03:49,590
Tiansheng Restaurant?

111
00:03:49,600 --> 00:03:51,430
Answer me first.
Have you been investigating me?

112
00:03:51,430 --> 00:03:52,816
I can book the place,

113
00:03:52,820 --> 00:03:54,752
but since it's official business,
you're paying.

114
00:03:55,280 --> 00:03:55,960
Getting in or not?

115
00:03:57,120 --> 00:03:57,680
I am.

116
00:03:58,680 --> 00:04:00,120
Why wouldn't I?

117
00:04:00,910 --> 00:04:02,120
This case

118
00:04:02,120 --> 00:04:03,648
(Tiansheng Restaurant)
was first tried

119
00:04:03,664 --> 00:04:04,890
by the Jingshi District Court.

120
00:04:04,928 --> 00:04:05,952
(Chief Justice Xie)
The Health Bureau

121
00:04:05,952 --> 00:04:07,240
(Chief Judge of the Supreme Court)
issued a report,

122
00:04:07,240 --> 00:04:08,710
ruling it an accidental homicide.

123
00:04:08,710 --> 00:04:11,630
The case was later appealed
to the Supreme Court.

124
00:04:12,590 --> 00:04:14,750
The prosecution called a witness,

125
00:04:15,310 --> 00:04:17,870
President Wu Tong of St. Anton Hospital.

126
00:04:18,040 --> 00:04:19,750
As a medical consultant,

127
00:04:19,750 --> 00:04:22,070
he testified that the victim died

128
00:04:22,070 --> 00:04:24,390
(Prescription)
from poisoning by pinellia.

129
00:04:24,390 --> 00:04:25,360
One's a Chinese physician,

130
00:04:25,370 --> 00:04:26,496
the other's a Western doctor.

131
00:04:26,500 --> 00:04:28,256
How could they possibly
understand each other?

132
00:04:29,120 --> 00:04:30,160
You'd be better off

133
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:32,390
dropping this case.

134
00:04:33,830 --> 00:04:34,510
Why?

135
00:04:37,120 --> 00:04:39,560
Your brother-in-law was involved.

136
00:04:39,560 --> 00:04:41,000
He can't escape responsibility.

137
00:04:45,160 --> 00:04:46,120
Two years ago,

138
00:04:46,160 --> 00:04:48,448
there was a fierce debate
inside and outside the government

139
00:04:48,464 --> 00:04:51,040
over whether traditional
Chinese medicine should be abolished.

140
00:04:51,870 --> 00:04:53,600
When Gu Xishan's case came to light,

141
00:04:53,600 --> 00:04:54,870
the public claimed

142
00:04:54,870 --> 00:04:56,830
Chinese medicine lacked standards

143
00:04:56,830 --> 00:04:58,800
and had cost a man his life.

144
00:04:59,264 --> 00:05:01,360
What does that have to do
with my brother-in-law?

145
00:05:02,070 --> 00:05:03,950
He led the reforms

146
00:05:03,950 --> 00:05:05,630
and was promoted to Director
soon afterward.

147
00:05:05,630 --> 00:05:07,600
You tell me whether
it has anything to do with him.

148
00:05:09,560 --> 00:05:10,680
Remember this.

149
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:13,430
Nothing involving the government
is ever a small matter.

150
00:05:13,430 --> 00:05:16,800
The cabinet always
protects its own people.

151
00:05:16,800 --> 00:05:17,920
Dig too deep,

152
00:05:17,920 --> 00:05:20,144
and you might cross
someone you can't afford to offend.

153
00:05:20,480 --> 00:05:23,120
Then the Zhao family
won't escape unscathed.

154
00:05:33,240 --> 00:05:33,870
Chief,

155
00:05:34,430 --> 00:05:36,560
you seem to have a sweet tooth.

156
00:05:39,310 --> 00:05:40,000
I'm used to it.

157
00:05:44,138 --> 00:05:45,000
Thanks, Chief.

158
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:49,680
Careful.

159
00:05:49,680 --> 00:05:50,390
Watch your step.

160
00:05:50,390 --> 00:05:51,070
Good liquor.

161
00:05:51,070 --> 00:05:52,830
That was a fine drink.

162
00:05:55,792 --> 00:05:57,000
Take care on your way home.

163
00:05:57,000 --> 00:06:00,020
(Tiansheng Restaurant)

164
00:06:05,870 --> 00:06:07,560
Take the case file back.

165
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:09,830
I'm out.

166
00:06:11,680 --> 00:06:13,390
Didn't you insist on

167
00:06:13,390 --> 00:06:14,560
joining this case?

168
00:06:14,560 --> 00:06:15,070
What?

169
00:06:15,070 --> 00:06:15,630
Scared now?

170
00:06:16,310 --> 00:06:17,120
Well,

171
00:06:17,920 --> 00:06:19,190
I only have one rule.

172
00:06:19,232 --> 00:06:20,592
I do things because they're fun.

173
00:06:21,160 --> 00:06:22,680
This isn't fun to me anymore.

174
00:06:25,270 --> 00:06:26,120
You were saying before

175
00:06:26,120 --> 00:06:27,510
that you weren't afraid of anything.

176
00:06:27,520 --> 00:06:28,980
If you've chickened out, just admit it.

177
00:06:28,992 --> 00:06:30,040
Stop trying to provoke me.

178
00:06:30,270 --> 00:06:31,430
It won't work.

179
00:06:31,830 --> 00:06:33,120
Let me give you some advice.

180
00:06:33,390 --> 00:06:34,630
The waters run deep.

181
00:06:35,680 --> 00:06:36,510
Be careful,

182
00:06:36,720 --> 00:06:38,270
or you might lose your life, too.

183
00:07:01,360 --> 00:07:02,800
Are you trying to scare me to death?

184
00:07:03,270 --> 00:07:04,920
How's your investigation going?

185
00:07:08,750 --> 00:07:10,680
Shichuan is tied to this case.

186
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:12,560
I'm sure he's hiding something.

187
00:07:12,870 --> 00:07:14,070
Seriously?

188
00:07:14,600 --> 00:07:16,750
Back then, it was
the Health Bureau's report

189
00:07:16,750 --> 00:07:18,160
that sent Gu Xishan to prison.

190
00:07:18,208 --> 00:07:19,310
I looked at the prescription.

191
00:07:19,360 --> 00:07:20,870
The pinellia dosage was normal.

192
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:22,270
Qing Miao must've done all this

193
00:07:23,190 --> 00:07:24,510
to avenge her father.

194
00:07:24,544 --> 00:07:26,680
Then what are we waiting for?
Go ahead and look into it.

195
00:07:26,736 --> 00:07:28,830
I've been looking for an excuse
to file for divorce.

196
00:07:28,880 --> 00:07:31,550
Every time I bring it up, Father starts
talking about the two families

197
00:07:31,560 --> 00:07:32,880
and tells me to think of old times.

198
00:07:32,890 --> 00:07:34,060
Now I've finally got my chance.

199
00:07:34,070 --> 00:07:36,480
The case isn't important.
If you want a divorce, go ahead.

200
00:07:36,680 --> 00:07:38,190
I always thought your fights

201
00:07:38,190 --> 00:07:39,560
were just the usual marital spats.

202
00:07:40,190 --> 00:07:41,310
But after seeing all this,

203
00:07:41,760 --> 00:07:42,800
you really should leave him.

204
00:07:43,630 --> 00:07:45,720
What do you mean?
You're not investigating anymore?

205
00:07:45,760 --> 00:07:47,690
Yuan Hong is dead set
on making a name for himself,

206
00:07:47,750 --> 00:07:48,830
and he's stubborn.

207
00:07:49,270 --> 00:07:50,800
I'm afraid that if he keeps digging,

208
00:07:50,832 --> 00:07:52,288
he won't just expose Wu Shichuan.

209
00:07:52,290 --> 00:07:54,040
Our family will
get dragged into it, too.

210
00:07:54,040 --> 00:07:55,270
Have you lost your mind?

211
00:07:55,270 --> 00:07:56,920
If Wu Shichuan is guilty,

212
00:07:57,040 --> 00:07:58,864
we should cut ties with him
as soon as possible.

213
00:07:58,890 --> 00:08:00,544
Not only will this case be investigated,

214
00:08:00,576 --> 00:08:01,904
but it'll also be investigated now.

215
00:08:01,920 --> 00:08:03,200
I'll investigate it.

216
00:08:03,264 --> 00:08:04,600
I just won't do it with Yuan Hong.

217
00:08:06,310 --> 00:08:07,120
Shouldn't we

218
00:08:07,560 --> 00:08:09,270
tell Father first?

219
00:08:09,750 --> 00:08:11,830
If you tell him,
he'll only try to smooth things over.

220
00:08:11,920 --> 00:08:12,720
True.

221
00:08:19,000 --> 00:08:19,600
How about this?

222
00:08:20,430 --> 00:08:22,160
I'll handle Father.

223
00:08:22,750 --> 00:08:24,830
If he asks, I'll tell him

224
00:08:24,830 --> 00:08:26,340
you're away running an errand for me.

225
00:08:26,680 --> 00:08:27,830
If you solve the case,

226
00:08:27,920 --> 00:08:29,240
he probably won't blame you.

227
00:08:29,310 --> 00:08:30,800
He might even see you in a new light.

228
00:08:32,240 --> 00:08:33,910
And if you don't solve it...

229
00:08:34,560 --> 00:08:36,030
You'll put in a good word for me?

230
00:08:36,480 --> 00:08:37,630
I'll say you fooled me, too.

231
00:08:37,630 --> 00:08:38,550
I was kept in the dark.

232
00:08:39,870 --> 00:08:41,480
Are you really my sister?

233
00:08:41,840 --> 00:08:42,840
Enough talking.

234
00:08:43,080 --> 00:08:44,270
What's your next move?

235
00:08:48,270 --> 00:08:49,480
Gu Xishan was well known

236
00:08:49,480 --> 00:08:50,270
in Beijing

237
00:08:50,510 --> 00:08:52,150
for treating abdominal swelling.

238
00:08:52,150 --> 00:08:53,776
The symptoms
were just like Wu Shichuan's.

239
00:08:54,120 --> 00:08:56,030
If Qing Miao was behind all of this,

240
00:08:56,320 --> 00:08:57,670
I think we're close to the truth.

241
00:09:00,337 --> 00:09:01,720
Can you go back to the Wu residence?

242
00:09:04,700 --> 00:09:07,620
(Peking Union Medical College)

243
00:09:07,744 --> 00:09:09,936
Mind you, the patient in Bed Two
is an official's wife.

244
00:09:09,940 --> 00:09:10,990
She's got quite a temper.

245
00:09:11,000 --> 00:09:12,150
Go easy on her during rounds.

246
00:09:12,150 --> 00:09:13,550
- Keep your voice down.
- Got it.

247
00:09:14,910 --> 00:09:15,790
You again?

248
00:09:15,790 --> 00:09:16,440
What again?

249
00:09:17,150 --> 00:09:17,720
Test them.

250
00:09:21,670 --> 00:09:22,910
Are you following me?

251
00:09:23,024 --> 00:09:25,510
If you weren't hiding something,
I wouldn't have to.

252
00:09:25,510 --> 00:09:26,080
Give it back.

253
00:09:26,670 --> 00:09:27,440
Give it back!

254
00:09:27,808 --> 00:09:29,720
Robbing an honest citizen
in broad daylight?

255
00:09:29,720 --> 00:09:30,870
You? An honest citizen?

256
00:09:31,150 --> 00:09:32,270
If you're covering this up,

257
00:09:32,270 --> 00:09:34,736
and Wu Shichuan's infectious disease
spreads across the city,

258
00:09:34,740 --> 00:09:36,590
causing an outbreak,
you'll be held responsible.

259
00:09:37,030 --> 00:09:38,030
Infectious disease?

260
00:09:38,390 --> 00:09:39,840
Wu Shichuan's constant bleeding,

261
00:09:39,840 --> 00:09:41,000
diarrhea, and rapid weight loss

262
00:09:41,000 --> 00:09:42,440
aren't from poisoning at all.

263
00:09:42,500 --> 00:09:44,450
It's some kind of
infectious digestive disease.

264
00:09:45,600 --> 00:09:47,080
If you didn't suspect something,

265
00:09:47,080 --> 00:09:47,960
why test his blood

266
00:09:47,960 --> 00:09:49,080
and stool samples?

267
00:10:02,200 --> 00:10:04,200
I just wanted to find out what he had.

268
00:10:04,200 --> 00:10:05,550
I had no idea it was this serious.

269
00:10:05,632 --> 00:10:07,080
If you don't get to the bottom of it,

270
00:10:07,080 --> 00:10:08,120
you're an accomplice.

271
00:10:08,440 --> 00:10:09,080
Of course.

272
00:10:09,184 --> 00:10:10,480
I will investigate it.

273
00:10:10,736 --> 00:10:12,240
I'm not taking the blame for this.

274
00:10:13,670 --> 00:10:14,320
I ran the tests.

275
00:10:14,550 --> 00:10:15,790
His blood was normal,

276
00:10:16,390 --> 00:10:17,670
but his stool...

277
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:18,600
What?

278
00:10:19,390 --> 00:10:20,510
It contains blood flukes.

279
00:10:20,864 --> 00:10:21,960
This disease is found mainly

280
00:10:21,960 --> 00:10:23,390
along the middle and lower Yangtze.

281
00:10:24,390 --> 00:10:25,510
Over a decade ago,

282
00:10:25,510 --> 00:10:27,280
there was a major outbreak
in Changde, Hunan.

283
00:10:27,328 --> 00:10:28,960
Since then,
there have been small outbreaks

284
00:10:29,080 --> 00:10:31,080
every flood season
along the Yangtze River.

285
00:10:31,080 --> 00:10:33,510
But I've never heard of

286
00:10:33,510 --> 00:10:34,624
a major outbreak in Beijing.

287
00:10:35,360 --> 00:10:36,750
Is it really contagious?

288
00:10:37,216 --> 00:10:38,752
It's highly infectious.

289
00:10:38,768 --> 00:10:41,070
Anyone whose skin comes into contact
with contaminated water

290
00:10:41,080 --> 00:10:41,770
can get infected.

291
00:10:41,960 --> 00:10:43,360
In severe cases, it can be fatal.

292
00:10:43,910 --> 00:10:47,030
But my brother-in-law said
he saw ghosts.

293
00:10:47,440 --> 00:10:49,030
Can blood flukes cause hallucinations?

294
00:10:50,550 --> 00:10:51,390
Not that I know of.

295
00:10:54,960 --> 00:10:56,720
We need to ask a master.

296
00:11:02,030 --> 00:11:02,790
Priest.

297
00:11:04,390 --> 00:11:05,080
Priest.

298
00:11:08,600 --> 00:11:10,480
Tell me exactly what happened
when you performed

299
00:11:10,490 --> 00:11:11,872
the exorcism on my brother-in-law.

300
00:11:13,030 --> 00:11:14,480
It was an evil spirit.

301
00:11:14,480 --> 00:11:15,960
I merely acted

302
00:11:16,440 --> 00:11:18,600
on Heaven's behalf.

303
00:11:22,448 --> 00:11:23,910
How about doing me a favor instead?

304
00:11:24,120 --> 00:11:24,790
Tell me.

305
00:11:27,030 --> 00:11:30,240
Heaven's secrets must not be revealed.

306
00:11:36,360 --> 00:11:37,030
Spill the beans.

307
00:11:46,270 --> 00:11:47,840
You're a rich young master in Beijing.

308
00:11:48,390 --> 00:11:49,600
That's all you're carrying?

309
00:11:50,150 --> 00:11:52,080
Why carry so much anyway?

310
00:11:55,790 --> 00:11:56,360
Speak.

311
00:11:58,200 --> 00:12:00,600
I'm a humble Taoist.

312
00:12:00,840 --> 00:12:03,360
You can't insult me
with worldly possessions.

313
00:12:05,480 --> 00:12:07,600
Take a closer look.

314
00:12:07,600 --> 00:12:09,030
It's a Patek Philippe.

315
00:12:10,200 --> 00:12:11,600
Patek Philippe!

316
00:12:11,840 --> 00:12:12,320
This...

317
00:12:19,790 --> 00:12:20,670
Mister,

318
00:12:21,080 --> 00:12:22,150
what is this?

319
00:12:22,440 --> 00:12:23,120
You see,

320
00:12:23,120 --> 00:12:23,870
I'm a fair man.

321
00:12:24,550 --> 00:12:25,550
One shot each.

322
00:12:33,720 --> 00:12:34,670
If I go down,

323
00:12:34,910 --> 00:12:35,840
you talk.

324
00:12:36,600 --> 00:12:37,550
If you go down,

325
00:12:38,120 --> 00:12:39,270
save it for your next life.

326
00:12:40,840 --> 00:12:41,840
I'll go first.

327
00:12:57,120 --> 00:12:58,200
Looks like fate's on my side.

328
00:12:58,840 --> 00:12:59,630
Your turn.

329
00:13:02,440 --> 00:13:03,510
Wait.

330
00:13:17,390 --> 00:13:18,390
You're a police officer.

331
00:13:18,390 --> 00:13:19,870
You can't just kill people.

332
00:13:21,120 --> 00:13:22,240
What's the big deal?

333
00:13:22,240 --> 00:13:23,390
It's only one life.

334
00:13:38,960 --> 00:13:39,870
Are you insane?

335
00:13:42,120 --> 00:13:43,030
Sorry.

336
00:13:45,120 --> 00:13:47,150
It's toad venom!

337
00:13:47,150 --> 00:13:47,750
What?

338
00:13:48,120 --> 00:13:50,270
Someone poisoned Director Wu
with toad venom.

339
00:13:50,270 --> 00:13:51,550
They scraped the toxin off a toad,

340
00:13:51,550 --> 00:13:53,030
dried it,

341
00:13:53,030 --> 00:13:54,080
and mixed it into his food.

342
00:13:54,080 --> 00:13:55,750
It causes hallucinations

343
00:13:55,750 --> 00:13:57,870
for about an hour.

344
00:13:58,320 --> 00:14:00,360
As for what he sees,

345
00:14:00,490 --> 00:14:00,910
that...

346
00:14:00,910 --> 00:14:02,870
That depends on
what guilty conscience he has.

347
00:14:03,550 --> 00:14:04,360
Misters,

348
00:14:04,750 --> 00:14:06,120
if you need any,

349
00:14:06,510 --> 00:14:07,440
I've still got some

350
00:14:07,440 --> 00:14:08,960
in stock.

351
00:14:11,000 --> 00:14:11,750
No thanks.

352
00:14:20,320 --> 00:14:21,080
Don't!

353
00:14:29,600 --> 00:14:30,600
From now on,

354
00:14:31,670 --> 00:14:32,670
stop scamming people.

355
00:14:33,150 --> 00:14:34,150
Do some good instead.

356
00:14:34,630 --> 00:14:36,030
Or one day,

357
00:14:36,360 --> 00:14:37,670
you'll run into ghosts.

358
00:15:08,600 --> 00:15:09,630
You did well today.

359
00:15:09,640 --> 00:15:11,840
That Taoist priest gave himself away
after a single bluff.

360
00:15:12,200 --> 00:15:13,480
I didn't do anything.

361
00:15:14,670 --> 00:15:16,320
You deserve the credit, Chief Yuan.

362
00:15:17,120 --> 00:15:18,320
All I did was find the priest.

363
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:19,910
What do you mean?

364
00:15:19,910 --> 00:15:21,030
Nothing.

365
00:15:21,600 --> 00:15:23,550
You're meant for great things,
Chief Yuan.

366
00:15:23,550 --> 00:15:24,360
Cool.

367
00:15:24,360 --> 00:15:25,630
Doesn't care about bullets

368
00:15:26,000 --> 00:15:27,080
and your own life.

369
00:15:28,360 --> 00:15:29,440
It was just expedient.

370
00:15:29,440 --> 00:15:30,120
Nothing more.

371
00:15:30,176 --> 00:15:31,550
Next time you do something like that,

372
00:15:31,550 --> 00:15:32,750
could you give me a heads-up?

373
00:15:40,030 --> 00:15:40,870
Not getting in?

374
00:15:41,536 --> 00:15:42,390
I'm in a bad mood.

375
00:15:42,976 --> 00:15:43,790
I'd rather walk.

376
00:15:46,620 --> 00:15:51,060
(Taixu Temple)

377
00:15:55,390 --> 00:15:56,576
Yuan Hong!

378
00:15:56,640 --> 00:15:59,320
You've got nine lives, don't you?
You're not afraid to die. Well done.

379
00:15:59,320 --> 00:16:00,320
You're something else.

380
00:16:00,320 --> 00:16:01,630
You don't need anybody.

381
00:16:01,630 --> 00:16:02,240
Fine.

382
00:16:02,550 --> 00:16:03,080
In that case,

383
00:16:03,080 --> 00:16:05,080
from now on,
your business is none of mine.

384
00:16:05,080 --> 00:16:06,630
We'll stay out of each other's way.

385
00:16:06,630 --> 00:16:08,270
Don't let me see you again.

386
00:16:54,320 --> 00:16:55,440
It's you?

387
00:17:14,270 --> 00:17:15,000
What?

388
00:17:15,000 --> 00:17:16,240
You want me to do it for you?

389
00:17:35,920 --> 00:17:37,160
I'm the one who got hurt.

390
00:17:37,200 --> 00:17:38,270
Why are you making noise?

391
00:17:41,310 --> 00:17:43,110
I'm empathetic.

392
00:17:47,400 --> 00:17:48,350
Why were you following me

393
00:17:48,350 --> 00:17:49,720
this late at night?

394
00:17:50,160 --> 00:17:51,480
Who said I was following you?

395
00:17:51,680 --> 00:17:52,750
Then what were you doing?

396
00:17:56,000 --> 00:17:57,830
You don't own the road.

397
00:17:58,330 --> 00:17:59,190
You can walk here,

398
00:17:59,360 --> 00:18:00,280
but I can't?

399
00:18:00,704 --> 00:18:01,790
Why are you following me?

400
00:18:02,200 --> 00:18:03,960
Who's following you?
This isn't your road.

401
00:18:03,960 --> 00:18:05,120
I can walk wherever I want.

402
00:18:13,830 --> 00:18:14,440
Uh...

403
00:18:16,000 --> 00:18:16,720
Well...

404
00:18:18,510 --> 00:18:21,750
how far were you from me just now?

405
00:18:22,960 --> 00:18:23,510
Not close.

406
00:18:24,790 --> 00:18:25,350
I see.

407
00:18:26,530 --> 00:18:27,030
Then

408
00:18:27,550 --> 00:18:29,440
did you hear anything?

409
00:18:31,400 --> 00:18:32,400
Does a dog barking count?

410
00:18:32,400 --> 00:18:33,480
No.

411
00:18:35,070 --> 00:18:35,790
Then

412
00:18:36,350 --> 00:18:37,350
it was dead quiet.

413
00:18:39,750 --> 00:18:40,510
You're done?

414
00:18:46,420 --> 00:18:50,420
(End of Episode 3)

415
00:18:51,400 --> 00:18:53,040
♪Side by side,
we journey through this life♪

416
00:18:53,040 --> 00:18:54,580
♪Troubled times
are but a laughing matter♪

417
00:18:54,580 --> 00:18:55,830
♪However, the world changes♪

418
00:18:55,830 --> 00:18:57,750
♪You'll still be by my side♪

419
00:18:57,750 --> 00:18:59,440
♪Side by side,
we journey through this life♪

420
00:18:59,440 --> 00:19:01,010
♪Praise and blame come and go♪

421
00:19:01,010 --> 00:19:02,580
♪If this is my final chapter♪

422
00:19:02,580 --> 00:19:05,080
♪I'll solve this mystery with you♪
